RESEARCH CONTRIBUTIONS OF PROF. VINOD PRASAD
IN BRAIN COMPUTER INTERFACE (BCI)

Vinod’s work addressed a number of research challenges in the design and develop BCI systems, which include robust signal processing and feature extraction algorithms for decoding motor and cognitive tasks, machine learning strategies for accurate classification, operating protocols and techniques for translating the neural inputs from the user into application-specific control signals. 

FUNDED RESEARCH PROJECTS IN BRAIN MACHINE INTERFACE AREA (ONGOING AND COMPLETED AS PRINCIPAL INVESTIGATOR)

